    "narrative": "The Austin Waves look poised for high-ceiling production today, anchored by **Gunnar Henderson** (83.29) and **Kyle Tucker** (78.72). **Gunnar Henderson** holds the day\u2019s highest score, benefiting from a massive 16% park adjustment and an aggressive lead-off spot against Roupp. Meanwhile, **Kyle Tucker** leverages a favorable matchup against Rocker, bolstered by 5mph wind blowing out and a stellar 0.372 xwOBA, keeping him in the elite tier despite a moderate SP_xERA. **Jackson Merrill** also provides a high-floor spark (75.10) against Sugano, capitalizing on a 17% boost from a favorable SP skill profile to drive his efficiency well above his baseline.\n\nStrategic depth is a core theme today, particularly in the outfield and bench management. **Andy Pages** (62.85) edged into the lineup, largely due to a slow SP delivery from Rocker that bolsters his stolen base potential, fitting our priority to aggressively chase speed. The most difficult bench decision involved **Nolan Schanuel** (47.94), who fell just shy of the active roster; despite a positive wind adjustment, his raw projection was dampened by the difficult matchup against Burns, pushing him behind the higher-efficiency profiles of our active starters. We are also monitoring the 38% rain risk for **Josh Lowe**, whose proximity to that storm window, combined with facing the toughest pitcher of the day (Burns, 2.76 xERA), makes his 51.62 score somewhat precarious.\n\nWe must remain vigilant regarding the volatile conditions in the **Miguel Vargas** game, where a 31% rain risk introduces significant uncertainty to his 51.96 score. While **Miguel Vargas** benefits from a strong lineup position, the weather warning makes him a leverage play. Elsewhere, we are leaning on our platoon strengths, particularly with **Liam Hicks** (59.93), who receives a significant 11% bump due to the favorable dynamic platoon split against Montero. We will continue to monitor the status of **Luis Robert Jr.** and **Luis Garc\u00eda Jr.**, who both hit the bench today due to unfavorable pitching matchups and efficiency scores that failed to break the 40-point threshold required for a start in this league format.",
